This paper deals with optimization algorithms for risk-sensitive objective functions in Markov decision processes (MDPs). The paper discusses the use of conditional value-at-risk (CVaR) as a risk measure, which is a popular topic in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses policy gradient and actor-critic algorithms, which are commonly used in control and optimization problems, suggesting that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper deals with optimal stopping problems, which are often studied in game theory, suggesting that cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as well.
